I have even written about Delvin Miller on TheStreet! thestreet.com/opinion/kass-h…
Hazel Park and everyother track in the US and in Europe! I was nuts!

My first horse with Delvin was Antonious Hanover, paid nothing for him, won alot and sold him well! Our most expensive purchase was Delmonico Hanover, full brother to Delmonica Hanover. Bought him privately for about $500k, he couldnt take a step forward - but was well bred!
I raced against Ed Ryan and knew Joe Hardy well. All Pittsburgh institutions.

Delvin was a good friend. For the first five years of my involvement in harness racing he was my trainer, driver and co owner! I used to stay at his place, Adios, near Pittsburgh and The Meadows was my favorite track. I loved Roger Huston's call of the races.
